ms of financial incentives for health behavior change.   You were randomly offered one of five possible conditions. Firstly, some of you were assigned to a control condition in which you only set a goal and received feedback about your progress. Additionally, in four experimental conditions we added different forms of financial incentives to this basic control condition: (1) an incentive where money could be gained with positive feedback about your earnings, (2) an incentive where money could be gained with negative feedback about your losses, (3) an incentive where money had to be deposited first and could then be regained with positive feedback about your earnings or (4) an incentive where money had to be deposited first and could then beregained with negative feedback about your losses.   We did not mention this in so much detail in the information letter, to be sure that your possible knowledge about this research could not influence your answers and thereby influence what we tried to learn.  If you were assigned to one of the financial incentive conditions where we asked for a personal deposit, there was an additional element of deception which we will now explain. Because we wanted to investigate the effect of possibly losing some of your own money, we informed you that (part of) your personal deposit could be lost based on your daily steps goal achievement. However, because we want to minimize the risk of financial damage we will refund the entire deposit for all participants. We did not mention this before or during the experiment because that would eliminate the motivating potential of this possible loss.   Your contribution to this research is important because we can learn more about what incentive programs may be effective to support healthy living. This allows us to develop effective incentive programs that can be added to interventions in order to support a healthy lifestyle.  If you want to continue to work on your lifestyle, you can continue using the Google Fit or Apple Health app that you have downloaded on your phone to track your physical activity.   If you have any questions about your medical situation we advise you to talk to your general practitioner for professional advice.  If you have any questions, or would like to know more about this research, please contact David de Buisonjé at the following e-mail address: d.r.de.buisonje@fsw.leidenuniv.nl.   You may also contact the principal investigator of this study, Thomas Reijnders, via email at t.reijnders@fsw.leidenuniv.nl or by phone: +31 71 527 2727. ; Group time: Hidden; Group time: ; Group time: .1; Group time: .2; Group time: .3; Group time: .4; Did you engage in less physical activity than usual due to the current situation with regard to the Corona-virus?","Please indicate to what extent you agree with the statements below. Please tick a box on the scale, where the value 1 means: ‘totally disagree’ and the value 10 means: ‘totally agree’ [The intervention was fair]: 5 | This does not apply | 1 = totally disagree | 2 | 7 | 8 | 10 = totally agree | 9 || Please indicate to what extent you agree with the statements below. Please tick a box on the scale, where the value 1 means: ‘totally disagree’ and the value 10 means: ‘totally agree’ [The intervention was fun]: 5 | 3 | This does not apply | 10 = totally agree | 2 | 7 | 9 | 4 || Please indicate to what extent you agree with the statements below. Please tick a box on the scale, where the value 1 means: ‘totally disagree’ and the value 10 means: ‘totally agree’ [The intervention was helpful]: 5 | 1 = totally disagree | 8 | 6 | 2 | 10 = totally agree | 9 | 7 || Please indicate to what extent you agree with the statements below. Please tick a box on the scale, where the value 1 means: ‘totally disagree’ and the value 10 means: ‘totally agree’ [The intervention was easy to use]: 5 | 1 = totally disagree | 4 | 8 | 6 | 10 = totally agree | 9 | 7 || Please indicate to what extent you agree with the statement